<h1>Data Catalogue</h1>
Browse datasets that are commonly used across DfE digital services.
Before creating a new dataset, check whether an existing dataset already exists and whether there is an authoritative source available.
Using shared datasets helps services remain consistent, reduces duplication and improves the ability to analyse and compare data across DfE systems.
<h2>DfE Reference Data Catalogue</h2>
The DfE Reference Data Catalogue contains reusable datasets maintained through the DfE Reference Data library.
These datasets are intended to be shared and reused across multiple services.
Examples include:
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>Countries and Territories</li>
  <li>HESA Domiciles</li>
  <li>Qualifications</li>
  <li>Degrees</li>
  <li>Degree Types</li>
  <li>Subject Specialisms</li>
  <li>Equality and Diversity Data</li>
  <li>Bank Holidays</li>
  <li>Common Aggregation Hierarchy (CAH)</li>
</ul>
Browse the catalogue to explore available datasets, definitions and implementation information.
View Reference Data Catalogue
<h2>Countries, Territories and Domiciles</h2>
Several datasets are available for country-related use cases.
<h3>Countries and Territories</h3>
Use for:
Nationality
Country of residence
Standard country selection
Most service implementations
<h3>HESA Domiciles</h3>
Use for:
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>higher education data</li>
  <li>HESA-related integrations</li>
  <li>domicile reporting requirements</li>
</ul>
Further information and dataset definitions are available through the DfE Reference Data Catalogue.
<h2>Schools</h2>
<b>Authoritative source:</b> Get Information About Schools (GIAS)
Use when your service requires:
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>school selection</li>
  <li>school validation</li>
  <li>school reporting</li>
  <li>school reference information</li>
</ul>
The full schools dataset is available through the GIAS "All Establishments Data" download.
<h2>Local Authorities</h2>
<b>Authoritative source:</b> Get Information About Schools (GIAS)
Local authority information is available from the schools dataset.
Use when your service requires:
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>local authority selection</li>
  <li>local authority validation</li>
  <li>geographic reporting</li>
  <li>local authority codes</li>
</ul>
<h2>Initial Teacher Training Providers</h2>
<b>Authoritative source:</b> Accredited Initial Teacher Training Provider List
Use when your service requires:
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>provider selection</li>
  <li>provider validation</li>
  <li>provider reporting</li>
  <li>teacher training service integrations</li>
</ul>
<h2>Datasets Used by Individual Services</h2>
Some datasets are currently maintained within individual services rather than as shared reference data.
These datasets may be useful to other services and could be considered for wider reuse in future.
<h3>Passport Issuing Authorities</h3>
A passport issuing authorities dataset is currently used by Apply for Qualified Teacher Status (QTS).
If your service requires passport issuing authority data, contact the SD Data Insights Team before creating your own dataset.
Understanding demand across services helps inform whether this dataset should become part of the DfE Reference Data Catalogue in the future.
<h2>Need Help?</h2>
Contact the SD Data Insights Team if:
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>you cannot find an appropriate dataset</li>
  <li>a dataset appears incorrect</li>
  <li>you need guidance on using a dataset</li>
  <li>you would like a dataset reviewed for inclusion within the DfE Reference Data Catalogue</li>
  <li>you are aware of a dataset used by another service that could benefit wider reuse</li>
</ul>
The team can help identify existing datasets, advise on appropriate sources and support greater consistency across DfE services.